olive oil
1 packet basmati rice
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 bag salad leaves
40 g butter
1 tomato
1 cucumber
1 packet pulled pork
1 packet tomato paste
¼ cup water
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Corn Chips
2 clove garlic
½ sachet Tex-Mex spice blend
1 packet BBQ sauce
½ tbs brown sugar
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt

• Boil the kettle. Half-fill a medium saucepan with the boiling water.
• Add basmati rice and a pinch of salt and cook, uncovered, over a high heat until tender, 12 minutes.
• Drain, return to the saucepan, then add chicken-style stock powder, salad leaves and 1/2 the butter. Stir to combine and cover to keep warm.

• While the rice is cooking, finely chop garlic.
• Roughly chop tomato and cucumber.

• Heat a large frying pan over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook pulled pork, breaking up with a spoon, until browned, 2-3 minutes.
• Add garlic, Tex-Mex spice blend (see ingredients) and tomato paste, cooking until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Remove pan from the heat, then add BBQ sauce, the brown sugar, the water and remaining butter. Stir to combine.

• In a medium bowl, add tomato, cucumber, a pinch of salt and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil. Stir to combine.
• Divide rice between bowls.
• Top with Tex-Mex BBQ pulled pork, tomato salsa and Greek-style yoghurt.
• Serve with corn chips.